HEADWORD: Leadhillite
<hw>Lead"hill*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A mineral of a yellowish or greenish white color, consisting of the
sulphate and carbonate of lead; -- so called from having been first
found at <etsep>Leadhills</etsep>, Scotland.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

